A government that has no regard for the fact that Omar Khadr was a mere teenager when the alleged crimes took place.
The only government that, despite signing the Geneva Convention, reneges on its word and lets a child soldier rot in inhuman conditions.
The only one who relies on a travesty of justice to establish the defendant's guilt.
For your information, UNICEF, Amnesty International and the Canadian Bar Association are calling for Omar Khadra to be returned to Canada to face a fair trial.
It is precisely this same government that turns a blind eye to torture: it cares little if a young adult is now psychologically destroyed, perhaps for ever, after so many years of abuse.
