The high price level of raw materials in plastics and chemicals led to a significant monthly increase of 1.6% in the products and chemicals sector.
Prices fell in the oil processing sector (1.4%), in the production of electrical tools and machinery (0.9%) and to a lesser extent in wood processing (0.1%)
The prices of paper production, publishing and printing activities remained unchanged.
In the other sectors of the manufacturing industry, prices increased by between 0.2% and 0.9%.
