The Elites in Danger
The phenomenon was already evident a few days ago when the House of Representatives voted against the $700 billion bailout plan launched by the White House: a significant part of Americans was, and is, more interested in punishing Wall Street than in saving the economy.
The New York Times yesterday confirmed that the current crisis is splitting the Republican Party, increasingly divided between its old, moderate East Coast soul, which is pro-federal institutions and pro-business, and its new, conservative soul, which is hostile to those in Washington and the financial world, strong especially in the Midwest and South.
